Sixty years ago, fifteen-year old Roman Ferencevych lived through the waning
months of World War II in war-shattered Berlin, far from his native Ukraine.
After the war, he found himself in the United States  -- a displaced person, a
refugee, and an American soldier. Here he shares his memories of that turbulent
time.
 
